1
00:01:48,912 --> 00:01:51,174
Let's split up and replenish
our traveling supplies.

2
00:01:52,736 --> 00:01:53,877
You'll be shopping too?

3
00:01:54,237 --> 00:01:56,119
You've assigned all the necessities to me.

4
00:01:56,859 --> 00:01:59,061
There's food, water,
other daily essentials.

5
00:01:59,762 --> 00:02:02,401
I'm a bit confused as to
what that leaves for you to buy.

6
00:02:02,425 --> 00:02:06,028
Herbs and things of the like.

7
00:02:07,798 --> 00:02:08,258
Great.

8
00:02:08,699 --> 00:02:11,340
That's the face she makes when
she's hiding something from me.

9
00:02:11,901 --> 00:02:14,282
I've known Mistress
Frieren for a long time.

10
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:16,784
Nothing good happens
when she makes that face.

11
00:02:17,845 --> 00:02:19,866
She's plotting to buy
something we don't need.

12
00:02:22,248 --> 00:02:23,248
Look what I got.

13
00:02:23,288 --> 00:02:24,986
What are you going to use that for?

14
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:28,152
A corrosive potion that
only dissolves clothing.

15
00:02:28,232 --> 00:02:29,232
Return it!

16
00:02:29,653 --> 00:02:30,734
Here, a history tome.

17
00:02:31,134 --> 00:02:32,835
There's value in traditional study.

18
00:02:34,910 --> 00:02:38,971
Well, maybe that last one
wasn't entirely unnecessary.

19
00:02:40,551 --> 00:02:41,551
Best of luck.

20
00:02:41,771 --> 00:02:43,011
I'll meet you at the inn later.

21
00:02:53,594 --> 00:02:56,170
We can't afford to waste
what meager funds we have.

22
00:02:56,194 --> 00:02:59,755
I'd better keep a close eye on her.

23
00:03:04,615 --> 00:03:09,536
An accessory shop?

24
00:03:09,596 --> 00:03:11,693
You should stop going
to sleep with wet hair.

25
00:03:11,717 --> 00:03:13,677
Really.

26
00:03:15,718 --> 00:03:23,718
I never thought she would
be interested in fashion.

27
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,640
She seems so conflicted.

28
00:03:27,548 --> 00:03:28,089
Huh?

29
00:03:28,469 --> 00:03:29,469
What's that face?

30
00:03:30,111 --> 00:03:33,912
In all these years, I've never seen
Mistress Frieren look so troubled before.

31
00:03:33,936 --> 00:03:34,936
Hmph.

32
00:03:55,861 --> 00:03:57,182
She certainly took her time.

33
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,865
I suppose one accessory doesn't hurt.

34
00:04:04,889 --> 00:04:07,847
It's better than heavy
bones or strange potions.

35
00:04:07,871 --> 00:04:14,416
I should probably get
back to my own shopping.

36
00:04:14,717 --> 00:04:17,019
Is there anywhere I can get
a good dessert in this town?

37
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,742
No way, now she's taking it too far.

38
00:04:21,752 --> 00:04:22,512
Try the tavern.

39
00:04:22,692 --> 00:04:24,413
It's over in the basement of that building.

40
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:25,733
You should ask there.

41
00:04:25,973 --> 00:04:26,973
I will, thanks.

42
00:04:27,773 --> 00:04:30,690
It's been months since I've
even seen a granule of sugar!

43
00:04:30,714 --> 00:04:31,714
Hmm...

44
00:04:52,329 --> 00:04:53,630
This must be the place.

45
00:04:54,471 --> 00:04:56,873
Does anyone know where I can
get a good dessert around here?

46
00:04:58,395 --> 00:05:00,977
Something tells me this
isn't a pastry-loving crowd.

47
00:05:02,118 --> 00:05:03,119
A dessert joint?

48
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,541
Do you realize who you're talking to?

49
00:05:08,564 --> 00:05:08,965
Oh no.

50
00:05:09,505 --> 00:05:13,469
You've stumbled upon the biggest
sweet teeth in town, lucky lady!

51
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:17,432
We'll find you a sugar fix near or far.

52
00:05:18,627 --> 00:05:20,129
I was not expecting that.

53
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:23,572
I would have thought you
lot too rugged for sweets.

54
00:05:23,992 --> 00:05:27,516
A bit of sugar fills us with the
energy we need to adventure on.

55
00:05:28,236 --> 00:05:30,058
So they're adventurers, then.

56
00:05:30,478 --> 00:05:33,461
Still, I'd say rugged is an understatement.

57
00:05:33,501 --> 00:05:37,225
Terrifying.

58
00:05:41,609 --> 00:05:43,411
She must be on her way to the restaurant.

59
00:05:47,581 --> 00:05:47,781
Huh?

60
00:05:48,262 --> 00:05:49,262
That's strange.

61
00:05:49,463 --> 00:05:51,265
She's heading in the direction of our inn.

62
00:05:51,585 --> 00:05:52,983
Did she give up on dessert?

63
00:05:53,007 --> 00:05:57,131
I'm not even close to done shopping.

64
00:06:01,076 --> 00:06:02,076
You're late.

65
00:06:02,617 --> 00:06:03,617
I'm sorry.

66
00:06:04,459 --> 00:06:05,459
No matter.

67
00:06:06,281 --> 00:06:07,281
Put down your things.

68
00:06:15,462 --> 00:06:18,304
I was thinking, it's been too
long since we've had a treat.

69
00:06:34,212 --> 00:06:35,409
What an incredible view.

70
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,634
A superb recommendation.

71
00:06:39,295 --> 00:06:40,295
I feel awful.

72
00:06:41,356 --> 00:06:43,137
It was wrong of me to ever doubt you.

73
00:06:43,978 --> 00:06:44,978
What do you mean?

74
00:06:47,562 --> 00:06:48,804
Choose whatever you would like.

75
00:06:50,025 --> 00:06:51,946
You're absolutely sure we can afford this?

76
00:06:52,947 --> 00:06:54,508
I've been saving up in secret.

77
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:57,567
So she is capable of saving.

78
00:06:57,591 --> 00:07:04,737
What will you order, Mistress Frieren?

79
00:07:05,318 --> 00:07:11,323
Let's see... Today I feel like...
You feel like Merkur Pudding, right?

80
00:07:14,383 --> 00:07:16,864
Tonight you feel like
Merkur pudding, don't you?

81
00:07:17,704 --> 00:07:18,704
How did you know?

82
00:07:19,145 --> 00:07:21,886
You travel with someone for
years and you pick up on things.

83
00:07:22,606 --> 00:07:23,666
I can just tell with you.

84
00:07:29,728 --> 00:07:31,469
I can't tell what any of you are thinking.

85
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:35,950
Then we should put in more effort
so you can get to know us better.

86
00:07:36,931 --> 00:07:39,432
My favorite food, for
starters, is a ruff omelette.

87
00:07:39,932 --> 00:07:40,932
Mine is grapes.

88
00:07:41,192 --> 00:07:42,613
The sour, the better.

89
00:07:43,248 --> 00:07:44,869
And mine is... Those, correct?

90
00:07:45,349 --> 00:07:47,430
You make that clear, you corrupt priest.

91
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:49,731
That is nothing to blush about.

92
00:07:50,091 --> 00:07:53,553
I find it disturbing that your vice
is a primary player in our tale.

93
00:07:55,754 --> 00:07:56,955
I'm sorry, Fern.

94
00:07:59,116 --> 00:08:00,637
What do you have to be sorry for?

95
00:08:00,677 --> 00:08:04,559
I realized I don't know
the first thing about you.

96
00:08:05,419 --> 00:08:08,821
So I... didn't know what
sort of present you would like.

97
00:08:14,478 --> 00:08:15,214
This is for me?

98
00:08:15,238 --> 00:08:17,819
I completely forgot it was my birthday.

99
00:08:28,563 --> 00:08:29,843
It's a hair ornament, right?

100
00:08:31,064 --> 00:08:32,504
It's absolutely perfect.

101
00:08:33,025 --> 00:08:33,565
Thank you.

102
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:34,625
I love it.

103
00:08:35,405 --> 00:08:36,405
I did well?

104
00:08:37,486 --> 00:08:38,202
Very well.

105
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:42,348
And because you're hopelessly dense when it
comes to these things, allow me to be clear.

106
00:08:44,063 --> 00:08:46,444
I am overjoyed that you're
trying to get to know me.

107
00:08:47,204 --> 00:08:48,725
That is a gift in itself.

108
00:08:50,626 --> 00:08:52,507
Simply trying means that much?

109
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:59,290
Maybe we should find you a spell
for understanding people's feelings.

110
00:09:09,495 --> 00:09:11,476
Hey Fern, are you ready to be off?

111
00:09:11,856 --> 00:09:12,856
Sure.

112
00:09:26,609 --> 00:09:27,829
Tell me the truth, Mistress.

113
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:31,170
Does our journey have a
notable purpose this time?

114
00:09:32,171 --> 00:09:32,967
Not especially.

115
00:09:32,991 --> 00:09:36,152
Hopefully we'll be able to find
some decent spells, though.

116
00:09:37,852 --> 00:09:43,694
That and, whenever possible, I'd like to retrace
the adventures I had with Himmel and the others.

117
00:09:45,335 --> 00:09:46,815
Before all signs of it fade.

118
00:09:47,816 --> 00:09:48,816
I see.

119
00:09:48,876 --> 00:09:52,157
Remembering those adventures,
it's very important to you, isn't it?

120
00:09:53,827 --> 00:09:54,827
I don't know.

121
00:09:55,348 --> 00:09:56,588
That's what I want to find out.

122
00:10:03,253 --> 00:10:05,291
It seems you've finally
grown taller than me.

123
00:10:05,315 --> 00:10:08,112
Well, I am sixteen.

124
00:10:08,136 --> 00:10:09,918
I could be your big sister.

125
00:10:10,938 --> 00:10:11,938
Is that right?

126
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:16,302
Our diets are largely the
same, so that can't be the culprit.

127
00:10:17,362 --> 00:10:18,362
How strange.

128
00:10:50,475 --> 00:10:52,677
Your defensive training
is coming along nicely.

129
00:10:55,459 --> 00:10:57,681
Now, let's put your work to the test.

130
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,432
I aimed for the gaps in your magic.

131
00:11:11,052 --> 00:11:12,914
If this were a real fight, you'd be dead.

132
00:11:14,135 --> 00:11:15,135
Right.

133
00:11:15,576 --> 00:11:17,978
How will you handle it this time?

134
00:11:33,757 --> 00:11:35,177
That is plenty for today.

135
00:11:44,061 --> 00:11:47,882
Defensive magic is powerful,
but it rapidly depletes your mana.

136
00:11:49,195 --> 00:11:53,363
Maintain defense over a large area,
and you'll exhaust your supply in seconds.

137
00:11:55,447 --> 00:12:00,156
Meaning that the best option is to cast it in
select locations at the precise moment of impact.

138
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:01,637
Exactly.

139
00:12:18,025 --> 00:12:20,526
We've been practicing
nothing but defense for ages.

140
00:12:20,867 --> 00:12:22,868
Yes, to improve your odds of survival.

141
00:12:23,488 --> 00:12:24,549
I guess that makes sense.

142
00:12:24,809 --> 00:12:28,851
Being able to cast one defensive spell can
protect you from most every offensive spell.

143
00:12:29,411 --> 00:12:30,972
It's eerie how powerful they are.

144
00:12:31,532 --> 00:12:35,215
So, you haven't read the tome
on magical history I gave you.

145
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:39,297
Magic is just as much about
theory as it is about practice.

146
00:12:40,678 --> 00:12:41,678
Fine.

147
00:12:41,918 --> 00:12:45,020
You leave me no choice but to
read it to you at bedtime every night.

148
00:12:46,017 --> 00:12:47,017
I'll read it myself.

149
00:12:47,677 --> 00:12:49,078
I'm not a child anymore.

150
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,040
Why is this village so special?

151
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,061
It's just another place
to find spells, right?

152
00:13:03,621 --> 00:13:05,481
No, unfortunately not.

153
00:13:06,581 --> 00:13:07,821
It's all up to the weather now.

154
00:13:08,602 --> 00:13:09,602
That it is.

155
00:13:10,202 --> 00:13:11,802
Could one of you gentlemen help us?

156
00:13:12,903 --> 00:13:13,903
It's an elf.

157
00:13:14,363 --> 00:13:15,363
That hair...

158
00:13:17,657 --> 00:13:20,300
Do you happen to be the
mage they call Frieren?

159
00:13:22,442 --> 00:13:23,442
How did you know that?

160
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:28,589
You're here to see the
place where Qual was sealed.

161
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:31,472
I'll show you the way.

162
00:13:33,254 --> 00:13:34,254
Qual?

163
00:13:34,475 --> 00:13:36,317
The Elder Sage of Corruption, Qual.

164
00:13:38,019 --> 00:13:43,001
He's a horrific demon, responsible for the
many atrocities that befell this region.

165
00:13:43,321 --> 00:13:47,542
About 80 years ago, Himmel the
hero and his party sealed him away.

166
00:13:50,323 --> 00:13:54,244
That seal doesn't have much time left, so
I'm here to defeat him before he's an issue.

167
00:13:55,004 --> 00:13:56,661
Where does your information come from?

168
00:13:56,685 --> 00:13:59,446
I don't recall telling anyone about this.

169
00:14:00,646 --> 00:14:06,428
Until about 30 years ago, Himmel always went
out of his way to pay our town an annual visit.

170
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:10,534
He told me it was to check
on the condition of the seal.

171
00:14:11,234 --> 00:14:13,274
He was always rather soft at his core.

172
00:14:13,854 --> 00:14:16,955
You were a frequent subject
of conversation between us two.

173
00:14:17,615 --> 00:14:20,535
We agreed you were quite
heartless for not checking on him.

174
00:14:21,256 --> 00:14:22,836
She's a touch cold.

175
00:14:23,176 --> 00:14:24,436
Yes, and then some.

176
00:14:24,876 --> 00:14:25,876
Sorry about that.

177
00:14:26,757 --> 00:14:30,737
But still, she's not so heartless that
she'd leave your village to its fate.

178
00:14:31,717 --> 00:14:34,598
When the seal is on the
verge of collapse, she'll appear.

179
00:14:36,203 --> 00:14:38,043
And it would seem he was right.

180
00:14:39,484 --> 00:14:39,900
Indeed.

181
00:14:39,924 --> 00:14:47,924
This is it?

182
00:15:03,649 --> 00:15:05,610
I was right to assume that it's unstable.

183
00:15:06,815 --> 00:15:10,356
I shall dispel the seal
tomorrow, then take care of Qual.

184
00:15:17,877 --> 00:15:21,018
You were the one who thought to seal
him away in the first place, weren't you?

185
00:15:22,198 --> 00:15:25,019
Why didn't you and the others
defeat him when you had the chance?

186
00:15:26,099 --> 00:15:28,720
The story isn't as enthralling
as you might guess.

187
00:15:33,301 --> 00:15:34,301
I couldn't beat him.

188
00:15:35,805 --> 00:15:40,087
All the Demon King's forces were formidable,
but Qual was an exceptional mage.

189
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:45,369
He developed Zoltrak, the first
piercing spell in the history of magic.

190
00:15:46,890 --> 00:15:51,812
It can pierce not only defensive spells,
but the most durable magic-resistant armors.

191
00:15:52,453 --> 00:15:54,854
It directly targets and destroys the body.

192
00:15:55,974 --> 00:16:03,974
It is said that in this region, 40% of their adventurers
and 70% of their mages were killed by Zoltrak.

193
00:16:07,855 --> 00:16:09,938
A spell with that much
power shouldn't exist.

194
00:16:10,759 --> 00:16:11,759
Agreed.

195
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,820
As would most.

196
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:14,284
It was too strong.

197
00:16:15,445 --> 00:16:18,469
And it was that strength that
caused it to backfire on him.

198
00:16:19,691 --> 00:16:20,972
What do you mean, backfire?

199
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:28,398
It's painfully clear that you
haven't read your history tome.

200
00:16:28,878 --> 00:16:31,079
You sure you don't need
nightly bedtime stories?

201
00:16:31,399 --> 00:16:32,399
I'll start reading now.

202
00:16:33,399 --> 00:16:33,739
Don't.

203
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,160
It's fine.

204
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:38,060
It's more important that
you get a good night's sleep.

205
00:16:39,221 --> 00:16:40,822
You'll see for yourself tomorrow.

206
00:16:47,384 --> 00:16:48,504
I'm dispelling the seal.

207
00:16:50,965 --> 00:16:52,325
You mustn't let your guard down.

208
00:16:58,274 --> 00:17:06,274
What the...

209
00:17:21,098 --> 00:17:24,000
Long time no see, Frieren.

210
00:17:24,881 --> 00:17:27,002
How many years has it been now?

211
00:17:28,103 --> 00:17:29,103
Eighty.

212
00:17:29,524 --> 00:17:31,686
No time at all, then.

213
00:17:32,887 --> 00:17:34,027
For us, perhaps not.

214
00:17:35,869 --> 00:17:38,010
What's become of the Demon King?

215
00:17:38,671 --> 00:17:39,671
We killed him.

216
00:17:40,152 --> 00:17:40,808
I see.

217
00:17:40,832 --> 00:17:44,211
Then...

218
00:17:44,235 --> 00:17:46,216
I shall avenge his death.

219
00:17:46,636 --> 00:17:48,598
Fern, cast a defensive spell.

220
00:17:50,267 --> 00:17:52,427
Zoltrak!

221
00:18:00,729 --> 00:18:03,250
Oh, what have we here?

222
00:18:04,010 --> 00:18:05,710
You blocked Zoltrak.

223
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:10,311
That defensive spell of
yours must be powerful indeed.

224
00:18:12,292 --> 00:18:15,788
Mistress Frieren, can you
please tell me what's going on?

225
00:18:15,812 --> 00:18:19,153
That was ordinary offensive magic.

226
00:18:20,487 --> 00:18:21,868
You just saw his life's work.

227
00:18:23,028 --> 00:18:27,550
Allow me to introduce you to Zoltrak,
the great killing magic of legend.

228
00:18:32,152 --> 00:18:35,414
Qual, your spell was simply too powerful.

229
00:18:37,815 --> 00:18:45,318
After you were sealed away, mages across the land studied and
analyzed Zoltrak until they had a complete understanding of it.

230
00:18:46,562 --> 00:18:54,562
In just a few years, your work was incorporated into humankind's magic system,
and new defensive spells with power like none before were developed in response.

231
00:18:58,330 --> 00:19:01,992
The magic resistance offered by equipment
has improved significantly as well.

232
00:19:03,013 --> 00:19:06,115
These advancements have made
Zoltrak a death sentence no longer.

233
00:19:07,876 --> 00:19:10,718
Your great weapon is now
ordinary offensive magic.

234
00:19:14,209 --> 00:19:18,212
It's rather remarkable how much humanity
can achieve in the span of 80 years.

235
00:19:18,993 --> 00:19:22,616
Qual, if you don't resist, I'll
grant you a painless death.

236
00:19:24,217 --> 00:19:27,680
It's interesting, but I
see what you've done.

237
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:33,985
Your defense attunes itself to my
magic, and then disperses its power.

238
00:19:34,565 --> 00:19:37,467
You have a complex spell indeed.

239
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:42,641
It must consume a great deal of mana!

240
00:19:42,781 --> 00:19:44,941
He figured out the
weakness of defensive magic.

241
00:19:45,682 --> 00:19:47,682
Fern, you know what to do, don't you?

242
00:19:48,982 --> 00:19:49,982
Yes.

243
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:51,483
I remember from our practices.

244
00:19:52,703 --> 00:19:54,804
Then I'm going to ask
that you protect me as well.

245
00:19:55,084 --> 00:19:58,265
Ha ha ha ha!

246
00:20:18,848 --> 00:20:23,350
Oh, the elf can fly.

247
00:20:23,550 --> 00:20:25,210
How fun.

248
00:20:25,710 --> 00:20:26,710
Zoltark.

249
00:20:26,891 --> 00:20:34,891
Frieren, that spell is mine.

250
00:20:59,262 --> 00:21:03,384
Because of you, our quiet village
can live in peace once more.

251
00:21:05,166 --> 00:21:06,166
I've seen that hat.

252
00:21:07,227 --> 00:21:08,044
This old thing?

253
00:21:08,068 --> 00:21:13,691
Around these parts, the sun
beats down on us all year long.

254
00:21:14,272 --> 00:21:15,473
Every farmer has one.

255
00:21:16,573 --> 00:21:18,995
I've seen this one, this exact straw hat.

256
00:21:25,865 --> 00:21:26,865
You.

257
00:21:27,165 --> 00:21:29,466
You're the little delinquent
who flipped up my skirt.

258
00:21:31,466 --> 00:21:36,067
Have you got a death wish, you brat?!

259
00:21:36,827 --> 00:21:40,448
I've been wanting to do that for
ages, but unlike you, I have self-control!

260
00:21:40,568 --> 00:21:42,889
You better not kill him.

261
00:21:43,089 --> 00:21:45,709
Gross.

262
00:21:49,490 --> 00:21:50,710
So you're still alive, then.

263
00:21:51,890 --> 00:21:54,771
Thanks to your visit, I'll
be able to live even longer.

264
00:21:56,010 --> 00:22:04,010
I'm glad I trusted Himmel's
words and waited for you to come.

265
00:22:10,421 --> 00:22:11,421
You saved them.

266
00:22:11,882 --> 00:22:13,323
They all seemed so thankful.

267
00:22:14,143 --> 00:22:15,905
Thankful, yes, but not to me.

268
00:22:17,446 --> 00:22:19,187
His prophecy came to pass.

269
00:22:19,247 --> 00:22:21,108
Himmel was who they believed in.

270
00:22:22,630 --> 00:22:24,151
I don't understand exactly.

271
00:22:25,036 --> 00:22:31,838
But it seems to me that the person
Himmel believed in all this time was you.

272
00:22:34,539 --> 00:22:35,800
What is it, Mistress?

273
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:36,920
Nothing.

